modules.description: This module implements a mutable doubly-linked list with operations for node-level manipulation (insertion, removal, value updates) and sequence management (creation, traversal, bulk transfers). It works with bidirectionally linked nodes and sequences that support efficient head/tail operations, left-fold aggregation, and predicate-based searches. Typical applications include implementing queues, deques, or dynamic buffers where elements need frequent reordering, incremental updates, or selective extraction based on conditions.
